
@startuml
skinparam linetype zigzag

class Provider {
  - name: String
  - location: String
}

class Cruise {
  - cruiseNumber: String
  - name: String
  - startDate: Date
  - endDate: Date
  + addEmployee(employee: Employee)
  + addGuest(guest: Guest)
  + addShow(show: Show)
}

class Employee {
  - name: String
  - ssn: String
}

class Guest {
  - name: String
  - isVIP: Boolean
}

class Ship {
  - name: String
  - numberOfDecks: Integer
  - length: Double
  - passengerCapacity: Integer
}

class Booking {
  - bookingNumber: String
  - bookingDate: Date
}

class TravelAgency {
  - name: String
  - address: String
}

class DestinationArea {
  - name: String
  - seaName: String
}

class Show {
  - title: String
  - duration: Integer
}

class Ticket {
  - ticketNumber: String
  - cruise: Cruise
  - guest: Guest
}

class Itinerary {
  - cruise: Cruise
  - destinationArea: DestinationArea
}

Provider "1" *-- "0..*" Cruise : organizes
Cruise "1" *-- "0..*" Employee : requires
Cruise "1" *-- "0..*" Guest : has
Cruise "1" *-- "0..*" Show : offers
Cruise "1" *-- "1" Ship : uses
Cruise "1" *-- "0..*" Booking : booked through
Booking "1" *-- "1" TravelAgency : made by
Cruise "1" *-- "1" Itinerary : heads for
Itinerary "1" *-- "1" DestinationArea : to
Cruise "1" *-- "0..*" Ticket : has tickets
Ticket "1" *-- "1" Guest : belongs to
Guest "0..*" --> "1" Ticket : has one per cruise
@enduml

### Explanation of Relationships:
- `Provider` organizes many `Cruise`s.
- A `Cruise` has many `Employee`s, `Guest`s, and `Show`s.
- A `Cruise` is associated with exactly one `Ship`.
- A `Cruise` can be booked via multiple `Booking`s from a `TravelAgency`.
- A `Cruise` has an `Itinerary` that points to a `DestinationArea`.
- A `Guest` can participate in multiple `Cruise`s but only has one `Ticket` per cruise.
- Each `Ticket` is tied to exactly one `Cruise` and one `Guest`.

